This paper is about neural natural language generation (NNLG) systems, which are commonly studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the impact of semantic noise on these systems, which is a problem that can be addressed using artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses state-of-the-art models, which are often studied in the field of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of data cleaning, which is a common topic in the field of software engineering (cs.SD).
